lead_paragraph: Following the liberation of Ramadi, Baghdad has experienced a return to the days when guerrilla tactics paralyzed the city.

byline.contributor: Reporting was contributed by Falih Hassan, Omar Al-Jawoshy and Ahmed Salah from Baghdad, and an employee of The New York Times from Diyala Province.

headline.print_headline: Rising Anxiety in Baghdad Tempers Gains Against ISIS in Iraq’s Provinces
headline.main: Gains Against ISIS Bring More Deaths Elsewhere in Iraq

snippet: Following the liberation of Ramadi, Baghdad has experienced a return to the days when guerrilla tactics paralyzed the city.
abstract: Many Iraqis have tempered their elation at news of victory over Islamic State forces in Ramadi, following attack by group in Baghdad, part of series of attacks group has made across globe in span of week; onslaught underscores concerns that military successes against group have not been accompanied by progress on issues that gave rise to group in first place.

keywords.name: organizations
keywords.value: Islamic State in Iraq and Syria (ISIS)
